<br>
This is the premier site for AO news, on a daily basis. It is also the home of the detail maps which I personally continue to use in spite of their being a bit dated. From the main page, look on the left menu for the &quot;maps&quot; link. Click on that to see a graphic layout of all the zones and cities in the game. Now click on the zone/city to take you to the page for that zone/city. Note the cities are those little blue squares.<br>
<br>
On that page will be a scribble of cryptic and mostly useless data, and usually 1-4 thumbnails of detail maps.<br>
<br>
Let's say you're looking for a shop in Omni-1 Trade, (commonly called just &quot;Trade&quot;). Click on the Maps link from the main page, look at the bottom of the map for the cluster of three little blue squares labelled Omni-1 Trade, HQ, and Entertainment (commonly called just &quot;Ent&quot;). Click on the top left one, labelled Trade. There are no less than 4 thumbnails on the Trade page, three of them useless! You want the dark one on the middle right, with the tooltip that says &quot;color shop map&quot;. Click on that and, HOLY JESUS, it's a map showing you where all those elusive goddam shops are at!<br>
<br>
As you will see, Trade boasts no less than *8* Basic Supermarkets. This was a big part of the reason why I bailed on clan long ago, and went Omni <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Your homework assignment, young jedi, is to compare this map with the local (Ctrl-6) in-game map, (run AO in a window, and Alt-Tab back and forth), and figure out which shape on the in-game map represents shops. It is almost always the same symbol, and once you recognise it, life gets a lot easier <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The above paragraph assumes that you're omni, and can get to Trade. If not, then you are excused ;p<br>
<br>
