<br>
Since--assuming you're Clan as you should be--you'll be starting in Tir, you need to get outside and get the hell away from Tir. It's not a good town to learn your way around (or for much of anything else). Run outside, experience the lag, then look up for the tallest building in Tir. That's the (former) Council of Truth Hall, and the woompas are nearby. Head that way and home in on the very tall antennas. Find the woompa to Athen and bid Tir a hearty goodbye and good riddance. <br>
<br>
Athen used to be Omni-2, so it's similar to the big Omni cities. From the woompa, head up the hill behind it and get your bearings. There are three basic stores in Athen (one more in W Athen in Athen Shire). Head towards the intact towers to the right of the statues and you're on shopping row. The buildings there say &quot;shop&quot; on them to help out a bit more. First one is basice, second advanced, third superior, fourth general, fifth general, six superior, then the last three (and one around the corner) are a mix of basic and advanced. Just too make it really interesting, there are two Miir outlets on the very fringes of all this. Enjoy. <br>
<br>
As an aside, I too have played as Omni, and I can't stand Omni-T. It does have everything, including a very healthy dose of lag. Unfortunately, it all looks the same and I never have gotten a real handle on which shops are on which side of what. It's also usually about pitch black, due to the canyon effect of the highrises. A pox on Trade. I prefer Rome. <br>
<br>
